# Project Context

This frontend belongs to a football prediction web application with a freemium subscription model.

Stack:
- Next.js with JavaScript.
- Material UI template already installed.
- Backend will be NestJS + Prisma + PostgreSQL.
- AI provider will be OpenAI.

Product goal:
Show daily football matches and AI-generated conservative betting recommendations. Free users can view 2 full predictions per day. Premium users can view all predictions, alternative picks, combo bets, stake index, history and performance.

The app is not a bookmaker and does not process real-money bets. It only displays analysis and lets users track picks internally.

Frontend rules:
- Reuse the current template structure, layouts, theme, MUI components and navigation system.
- Do not replace the purchased template architecture.
- Keep critical access rules on the backend. Frontend blur is only visual.
- Do not hardcode secrets.
- Use environment variables for API URLs.
- Keep API access in services, not inside deeply nested UI components.
- Use mock data only while backend endpoints do not exist.

Prediction rules:
- Never display words like guaranteed, sure, fixed, safe bet, free money or apuesta segura.
- Confidence values are HIGH, MEDIUM, LOW and NO_BET.
- Stake is a 0-100 index, not a direct percentage of the bankroll.
- The system should allow NO_BET when risk is high or value is unclear.
